"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The method `ax.set_xticks` expects a list of numerical values (positions) where the ticks should be placed, not the actual datetime values. Additionally, `ax.set_xticklabels` should be used to set the labels for these positions. The current code is trying to set datetime values directly as tick positions, which is incorrect.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19,20\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n<ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n>ax.set_xticks(range(len(df.date.unique())))\\n>ax.set_xticklabels(labels=[d.strftime('%Y-%m-%d') for d in df.date.unique()], rotation=45)\"\n}"